Cascade-wide CI defect cluster (witnessed across all 6 repos): release/publish workflows delete Cargo.lock and regenerate per build (non-reproducible, upstream drift ships with no local commit to bisect); rs-plugkit Cargo.toml pulls rs-learn/rs-search from unpinned main; npm publish steps are continue-on-error plus ||echo (failed ships invisible); auto-bump uses git rebase -X theirs (can silently discard concurrent main commits); rs-learn/rs-search cascade+publish paths-ignore miss .gm/** so gm bookkeeping chore commits trigger full wasm releases (rs-learn 0.1.78 through 0.1.81 all chore-produced); gm publish.yml test job runs the pre-bump sha while publish jobs checkout post-bump ref:main (tested tree != shipped tree); single PUBLISHER_TOKEN is the entire ship path; rs-learn tests run on PR only under a direct-push-to-main policy so production wasm ships untested.